THE YGUARo, οη WATERJrIGER.

This beast‚ which is larger than a mastiff, is generally concealed under deep water. It is shaggy, with a long tail, ending in a point, and is armed with very strong nails, It lays hold of horses and muleS, as they are swimming across rivers, and drags them to the bottom. Shortly after, the bowels of the animal, which it has torn to pieces, are seen floating on the surface of the water. The yaguaro generally dwells in deep gulphs of rivers, but digs large caverns in the higher banks, where it can hide both itself and its offspring.
